If the given points are $$ P_{1} = (x_{1}, y_{1}) $$ and $$ P_{2} = (x_{1}, y_{1}) $$ and if $$P = (x,y)$$ is the midpoint then:

$$
x = x_{1} + \frac{1}{2}(x_{2}-x_{1})
$$
$$
y = y_{1} + \frac{1}{2}(y_{2}-y_{1})
$$
Therefore:
$$
x = \frac{1}{2}(x_{1}+x_{2})
$$
$$
y = \frac{1}{2}(y_{1}+y_{2})
$$